cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on email spoofing attacks and their impact on email security. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper includes extensive user studies to evaluate the effectiveness of email provider warnings. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the protocols used by email providers to detect spoofing. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a potential category as the paper examines the impact of email spoofing on users and their behavior. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of UI design on user perception of email authenticity.
